[[File:Gnome (Mourner Headquarters) chathead.png|left]]
The '''Gnome''' (real name unknown) is a character, who is being tortured on a [[Rack (Mourner Headquarters)|rack]] by the [[Mourners]] in Mourner Headquarters in [[West Ardougne]]. He is involved in [[Mourning's End Part I]], where it is revealed that he can [[Fixed device|fix a device]] needed to re-dye some [[sick-looking sheep]]. The player will threaten to take out his wisdom teeth, which he replies that gnome do not have any wisdom. By using a feather on him to tickle his feet and bribing him with [[toad crunchies]], he will ask the player for a piece of [[soft leather]] and a [[magic log]] to repair it.

In [[Song of the Elves]], the Gnome is still kept hostage in the Mourner Headquarters when the revolutionaries break in and kill the Mourners. He cheers the revolutionaries on and is promptly freed by them. Following the end of the quest, he still remains in the headquarters, searching for any useful items the Mourners may have left behind.

